==English==

===Noun===
'''makeweight'''
# something of inferior quality which is included in a shipment to make up the weight

====Quotations====
*'''1893''': I would advise you to accept these as an instalment of a volume, (they are not big enough to make one themselves) with the promise that the stories to come should be more striking, more original in theme &mdash; not less so, not mere '''makeweights''' &mdash; than those under consideration. &mdash; Richard Le Gallienne, in a publisher's report on stories by Ernest Dowson, quoted in Jad Adams, ''Madder Music, Stronger Wine,'' page 88.

